## Building the image with live-helper

The most important elements of building Webconverger are:

1. [The package lists](http://git.debian.org/?p=debian-live/config-webc.git;a=tree;f=webconverger/config/chroot_local-packageslists)
2. [LH_BOOTAPPEND in config/binary](http://git.debian.org/?p=debian-live/config-webc.git;a=blob;f=webconverger/config/binary)

[live-initramfs lists the parameters](http://git.debian.org/?p=users/daniel/live-initramfs.git;a=blob;f=manpages/live-initramfs.en.7.txt;)


## Building on a Debian system:

 * apt-get install [live-helper](http://packages.qa.debian.org/l/live-helper.html) or rather use the latest from 'deb http://live.debian.net/debian-snapshots/ ./'
 * `git clone git://git.debian.org/git/debian-live/config-webc.git`
 * webconverger/ is the base config file. Have a look around.
 * Take a look inside config/. You probably need to edit LIVE_MIRROR variables in the file bootstrap.
 * lh build in webconverger/

Please [contact hendry](http://hendry.iki.fi/) if you have any suggestions/comments/fixes/patches. :)

 * Read [Testing setup guide](http://wiki.debian.org/DebianLive/Howto/Creating_a_Test_environment)
 * Join the [Debian Live](http://debian-live.alioth.debian.org/) community. See the [dev mailing list archives](http://lists.alioth.debian.org/pipermail/debian-live-devel/)

Tips:

 * [squid](http://packages.qa.debian.org/s/squid.html) saves bandwidth whilst Debian Live's live-helper downloads the packages

